/i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAl-Masudi&amp;rft.atitle=Saudi+Aramco+World+%3A+++++++++The+Model+of+the+Historians&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=saudiaramcoworld.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.saudiaramcoworld.com%2Fissue%2F200502%2Fthe.model.of.the.historians.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Shboul. <i>Al-Mas\'udi and His World</i>, pp. 68\xe2\x80\x9369.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Mas\'udi. <i>The Meadows of Gold, The Abbasids</i>, p. 14.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Shboul. <i>Al-Mas\'udi and His World</i>, pp. 29ff.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Devin_J._Stewart" title="Devin J. Stewart">Devin J. Stewart</a>, "Muhammad b. Jarir al-Tabari\'s <i>al-Bayan \'an Usul al-Ahkam</i> and the Genre of Usul al-Fiqh in Ninth Century Baghdad," pg. 333. Taken from <i>Abbasid Studies: Occasional Papers of the School of Abbasid Studies, Cambridge, 6\xe2\x80\x9310 January 2002</i>. Edited by James Montgomery. <a href="/wiki/Leuven" title="Leuven">Leuven</a>: Peeters Publishers and the Department of Oriental Studies, 2004.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See <span class="languageicon">(in Armenian)</span> Ter-Ghevondyan, Aram N. "\xc2\xab\xd4\xb1\xd6\x80\xd5\xa1 \xd6\x87 \xd5\x87\xd5\xa1\xd5\xb4\xd5\xab\xd6\x80\xd5\xa1\xd5\xb4\xc2\xbb \xd5\xa1\xd5\xbc\xd5\xa1\xd